<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The problem is that it runs into "Cannot redeclare class XXX" on windows.</p>

<p>Run this code:
require_once 'Zend/Loader.php';
Zend_Loader::registerAutoload();
new Zend_Session_Namespace();</p>

<p>The same file will be included again because it's loaded once using autoloader ('\') and once using script's require ('/').</p>

<p>I would suggest to require files within scripts using DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR. Or change behaviour of Zend_Loader::loadClass to use simple slash as we're already easy on this in script files and doesn't care about OS differencies.</p>

